		<b>Comment By vicky c, 4-23-10</b>
		<p>I agree,  Peter  Hessler's article in the New Yorker was great,so much so that I was compelled to read it aloud to my husband. He is a very funny and insightful author,who makes his stories come alive. I can't wait to read his new book,Country Driving.I have given my copy of River Town to many,and all have enjoyed it. I have travelled to many countries,but have never been to China. I  feel like I have,though,thanks to Hessler.</p>
		
